{"type":null,"faqId":26413,"title":"Miss understanding About Phone Maintenance","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\ncolor:#333333\">Misunderstanding About Phone Maintenance</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Have you ever heard of the following\nsayings about phone maintenance? And are they true?</span><span style=\"font-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\ncolor:#333333;\n\"> </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';color:#333333;\n\">Turning on the flashlight for too long will burn the\nflash. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Truth: The flash next to the camera is an\nLED whose lifespan is up to tens of thousands of hours. So you can be assured\nthat using your phone as a flashlight at night will not cause any damage to\nyour phone. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';color:#333333;\n\">The higher the camera resolution, the better the photo\nquality. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Truth: The camera resolution determines the\nphoto size only. It is the light sensing component that determines the photo\nquality. The more light received by each pixel, the better the photo quality. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';color:#333333;\n\">Power saving applications can effectively save the\nbattery power.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Truth: The only function of power saving\napplications is to remind you to disable some unnecessary functions and close\nbackground applications and processes that have been idle for a long time.</span><span style=\"font-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\ncolor:#333333;\n\"> </span><span style=\"\nfont-family:'minorBidi','serif';color:#333333;\">Some power\nsaving applications may even increase power consumption by monitoring power\nconsumption statistics and taking up system resources. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';color:#333333;\n\">The phone will explode if you charge it all night long. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Truth: This saying is similar to\n\"long-time charging will damage the battery\", which does not have any\nsubstantial evidence. Most smartphones nowadays adopt Li-ion batteries that\nautomatically disconnect from power sources once fully charged. Therefore, they\ndo not have such issue as over-charging. Your phone will not explode if you use\nthe original charger. </span></p>\n<br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"792","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433163682000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":2,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Miss understanding About Phone Maintenance","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}